    \"url\": \"https://x.com/moskstraum21745/status/2029574513017434398\",
    \"text\": \"I'm working on an even more powerful inference algorithm, upon which I bestowed the name Speculative Speculative Speculative Decoding  (SSSD).\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/araimonokaiy/status/2029555497263886534\",
    \"text\": \"新しいLLM推論アルゴリズムの開発に取り組んできました。  Speculative Speculative Decoding (SSD) という名前で、世界で最も強力な推論エンジンよりも最大2倍高速です。\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/IndraVahan/status/2029473972103061982\",
    \"text\": \"honestly i love how this was just named “speculative speculative decoding” and not something like “parallel speculative decoding” or “cascaded async speculative decoding”\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/sanskxr02/status/2029468422732697651\",
    \"text\": \"Can’t wait to drop my work on speculative speculative speculative decoding\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/askalphaxiv/status/2029451104027652209\",
    \"text\": \"“Speculative Speculative Decoding”\\n\\nEven though speculative decoding speed up LLM inference, it still has a hidden “stop-and-wait” step, where the draft model can’t start the next guess until the big model finishes verifying the last one.\\n\\nThis paper fixes that by making drafting and verification run in parallel. \\n\\nThe draft model precomputes speculations for the most likely verification outcomes while verification is happening, so when the outcome lands, the next tokens are ready instantly.\\n\\nThis cuts the overhead and delivering up to ~2x faster than optimized speculative decoding and ~5x over plain autoregressive decoding!\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/gpusteve/status/2029451093403713624\",
    \"text\": \"no no. u forgot about decoding speculative speculative decoding\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/webxos/status/2029412965078704487\",
    \"text\": \"Tanishq Kumar, Avner May, and Tri Dao have introduced Speculative Speculative Decoding, or SSD, a new algorithm that accelerates large language model inference by up to twice the speed of current top engines like vLLM and SGLang. https://t.co/e79XKTfTS4\"
  },
  {
    \"url\": \"https://x.com/SmitBPatel2/status/2029406506051833917\",
    \"text\": \"I read a new paper called “Speculative Speculative Decoding” (arXiv:2603.03251).\\n\\nThe problem is simple: large language mathematical systems generate text one token at a time. That sequential loop becomes the bottleneck during inference, even on powerful GPUs.\"
  }
]

